   <concept id="FAR_16_303" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " xtrc="">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">16.303</ph> Cost-sharing contracts.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d989e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1017e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Description.</i> A cost-sharing contract is a cost-reimbursement contract in which the contractor receives no fee and is reimbursed only for an agreed-upon portion of its allowable costs.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1017e17">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Application</i>. A cost-sharing contract may be used when the contractor agrees to absorb a portion of the costs, in the expectation of substantial compensating benefits.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1017e24">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Limitations</i>. See <xref href="16.301-3.dita#FAR_16_301_3"
                        base="i1104650"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">16.301-3</xref>.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
